Hello. I was wondering it would be nice project to allow users search for products using filters and categories, just as it's done by the website;

![untitled](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/25305892/37467064-83501d36-281c-11e8-9026-ce85f50dc001.png)


A user might just come to the app to search for product he/she can't remember. So if I type "broccoli", the app just gives hundreds of results, most not relevant to the location, store, and other preferences that I look for. Would be great to filter the results. Also, to build graphs and statistics as the website allows.

**Code:**

```java
for (Allergen a : mAllergensFromDao) {
            if (Locale.getDefault().getLanguage().contains("fr")){
                if(a.getIdAllergen().contains("fr:")) allS.put(index, a.getName().substring(a.getName().indexOf(":")+1));
            } else if (Locale.getDefault().getLanguage().contains("en")) {
                if(a.getIdAllergen().contains("en:")) allS.put(index, a.getName().substring(a.getName().indexOf(":")+1));
            }
            index++;
        }
```
Here in this code, we're only abstracting English and French allergens. However, I've checked allergens of other languages are also present in AllergenDao so instead of just these two languages we should check for each language which has been chosen by the user.

I've already fixed this and going to send a PR soon.

When adding a new product, 3 fields are displayed:
```
- Take front image
- Take nutrition image
- Take ingredients image
```

